id":"recZUsA9hFqEn5itY","ref":"Amos.3.1","text":"Hear this word that the LORD hath spoken against you, O children of Israel, against the whole family which I brought up from the land of Egypt, saying,","year":-787},{"id":"rec2Mgce7DTx40r06","ref":"Amos.3.2","text":"You only have I known of all the families of the earth: therefore I will punish you for all your iniquities.","year":-787},{"id":"rec7t8do8ZoqXakFa","ref":"Amos.3.3","text":"Can two walk together, except they be agreed?","year":-787},{"id":"recC4nSKx0VOfRffG","ref":"Amos.3.4","text":"Will a lion roar in the forest, when he hath no prey? will a young lion cry out of his den, if he have taken nothing?","year":-787},{"id":"recNpB5BdjZIPIyig","ref":"Amos.3.5","text":"Can a bird fall in a snare upon the earth, where no gin is for him? shall one take up a snare from the earth, and have taken nothing at all?","year":-787},{"id":"recH3GThRk8v9zMm5","ref":"Amos.3.6","text":"Shall a trumpet be blown in the city, and the people not be afraid? shall there be evil in a city, and the LORD hath not done it?","year":-787},{"id":"recGFJP7r87aYf5Eo","ref":"Amos.3.7","text":"Surely the Lord GOD will do nothing, but he revealeth his secret unto his servants the prophets.","year":-787},{"id":"recG56RBTZLW7BJxh","ref":"Amos.3.8","text":"The lion hath roared, who will not fear? the Lord GOD hath spoken, who can but prophesy?","year":-787}]}
